In CSS, you can align a row of `div` elements to the right using Flexbox with the `flex-direction: row-reverse;` property. Here's how you can do it:

```css
.container {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: row-reverse;
}

.box {
  width: 50px;
  height: 50px;
  background-color: #333;
  margin: 10px;
}
```

This will reverse the order of the `div` elements in the row, placing them from right to left. Each box has a width and height of 50 pixels and a margin of 10 pixels on each side.

